## Pre-commit and CI

- **Pre-commit** (`.pre-commit-config.yaml`) is the local quick gate: linting and formatting on all source files, plus a fast unit-only test run filtered by changed files. Install with `pre-commit install` once per clone.
- **CI** is authoritative. It runs the test and lint jobs on every PR and push to `main`/`master`; no PR merges without green CI.

If pre-commit and CI disagree, **CI wins** — pre-commit may be skipped or run a narrower subset, but no PR merges without green CI.

**The gate is the integration suite.** Unit tests mock the DB/serialization/HTTP boundaries and cannot catch ORM↔domain mismatches, schema regressions, or migration failures. Before claiming any non-trivial change done, run the full integration suite. Also run the full frontend suite if applicable.

