## Task schema

A plan is an ordinary Markdown document with `## Task N` (or `### Task N`) headings. To make a task machine-verifiable, **augment** it with a `task-meta` HTML-comment block declaring `id`, `touches`, `depends`, `verify`, and optionally `acceptance`. `run_task.py` then runs that task's `verify` and ticks its checkbox; a task with no `task-meta` block is human-run and ignored by the harness. It is an augmentation of a normal plan, not a separate plan format. See [`docs/task-schema.md`](docs/task-schema.md).

Validate any plan locally with:

```bash
python scripts/harness/validate_plan.py docs/plans/<file>.md
```

---

## Harness tooling

Five scripts extend the execution harness. All exit `0` on success, `1` on a real failure, `2` on a usage error. Plans live in `docs/plans/`.

- **Parallel scheduler** — `python scripts/harness/plan_schedule.py <plan.md>`
  prints the topological *layers* of a plan (tasks in the same layer have no dependency between them and may run in parallel) and fails if two same-layer tasks declare the same path in `touches`.
- **Doc-freshness check** — `python scripts/harness/check_freshness.py <file.md> …`
  flags expired `<!-- freshness: YYYY-MM-DD ttl: Nd -->` markers. Annotate any dated claim with a marker; the check fails once `date + ttl` is in the past. Runs as the advisory `doc-freshness` pre-commit hook.
- **Cycle closer** — `python scripts/harness/cycle_done.py --plan <file>`
  closes a work cycle: verifies all tasks are checked off **and** every command in `.harness/gates` exits 0, then appends an `[Unreleased]` entry to `CHANGELOG.md`. `.harness/gates` holds one shell command per line (the project's test / lint / typecheck / build commands). To bypass with an audit trail, use `--force -m "<reason>"` (logged to `.harness/exceptions.log`).
- **Plan validator** — `python scripts/harness/validate_plan.py <plan.md>`
  validates task-meta blocks for schema correctness, unique ids, dependency cycles, and write-collision conflicts.
- **Task runner** — `python scripts/harness/run_task.py <plan.md> <task-id>`
  runs a task's `verify` command and ticks its checkbox in the plan file on success.

A cycle is "done" only when `scripts/harness/cycle_done.py --plan <file>` exits 0.

